# Literature Review: Opportunities Challenges and Implications of Generative Conversational AI for Research Practice and Policy

## Introduction

Generative Conversational AI, exemplified by ChatGPT, has emerged as a powerful tool with the capacity
to carry out remarkably complex tasks. This paper aims to provide a comprehensive review of the potential
opportunities, challenges, and implications of generative conversational AI in various domains, including
healthcare education, research, and practice. By synthesizing the existing research findings, this review
aims to shed light on the promising perspectives of ChatGPT while also addressing valid concerns
associated with its use.

## Potential Applications in Health Care Education, Research, and Practice

The potential applications of ChatGPT in healthcare education, research, and practice have been widely
recognized. Sallam (2023) conducted a systematic review and highlighted the promising perspectives of
ChatGPT in these domains. The author emphasized that ChatGPT can contribute to healthcare education
by providing personalized learning experiences and facilitating knowledge exchange among students
and healthcare professionals. Furthermore, ChatGPT can assist in medical research by automating data
analysis, literature review, and hypothesis generation. In healthcare practice, ChatGPT can support clinical
decision-making, patient triage, and telemedicine consultations. However, the author cautions that valid
concerns associated with the use of ChatGPT in healthcare should be proactively examined and addressed
to ensure its safe and effective implementation.

## Capacity and Growth of ChatGPT

ChatGPT has taken the world by surprise with its sophisticated capacity to perform complex tasks. Its
ability to understand, generate, and respond to human-like text has garnered significant attention and
appreciation (Semantic Scholar, 2023). The exponential growth of ChatGPT is evident from the fact
that it has reached over 100 million users, making it the fastest-growing consumer application to date
(Baidoo-Anu & Ansah, 2023). This growth reflects the widespread adoption and acceptance of ChatGPT
as a valuable tool in various domains, including education, research, and practice.

## Revolutionizing Medical Writing

One specific area where ChatGPT can have a transformative impact is medical writing. Liu, Lee,
and Lee (2020) argue that ChatGPT can revolutionize the process of medical writing by making it
quick and time-efficient. The authors highlight that medical writing often involves complex terminology
